Package chainParticipants

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Party  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChainParticipant
    An abstract class describes the general state and behavior of a participant in a chain, including operations such as accepting a product, fulfilling a request, accepting payment, and others.
    Customer
    The class describes the state and behavior of the buyer.
    Farmer
    The class describes the general state and behavior of a farmer.
    Manufacturer
    The class describes the behavior of a manufacturer capable of creating certain types of products based on requests and the availability of available ingredients.
    MeatFarmer
    The class describes the behavior of a farmer producing meat products.
    Retailer
    The class describes the behavior of a retailer.
    Seller
    The class describes the behavior of a seller like a wholesaler.
    Storehouse
    The class describes the behavior of a warehouse with three types of refrigerators.
    VegetableFarmer
    The class describes the behavior of a farmer producing vegetable products.
